<subSubSection id="FF6DD26F628AF3024A6008D0DABDBE37" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="notes">
<paragraph id="BCB3584256AAB786B460C7A0CF50D6DF" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C7DF8030D12CDE57083ABCC94024C356" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
In the last revision of 
<taxonomicName id="E10ABA9E992C4B0059294F464194AF10" baseAuthorityName="Andre" baseAuthorityYear="1881" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Cataglyphis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cataglyphis livida" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="livida">
<emphasis id="55301094EA19C304F3D92DA6E56894AA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Cataglyphis livida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex, 
<bibRefCitation id="7E04D9DDF63832DF1F679D0FD0DCA08A" author="Salata, S." journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" pagination="117 - 131" refId="B7725961" refString="Salata, S., Kiyani, H., Minaei, K., Borowiec, L., 2021. Taxonomic review of the Cataglyphis livida complex (Hymenoptera, Formicidae), with a description of a new species from Iran. ZooKeys 1010: 117 - 131" title="Taxonomic review of the Cataglyphis livida complex (Hymenoptera, Formicidae), with a description of a new species from Iran" volume="1010" year="2021">Salata et al. (2021)</bibRefCitation>
proposed 
<taxonomicName id="965A6ACD3B1971C03A36565EF338AAF3" baseAuthorityName="Andre" baseAuthorityYear="1881" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Cataglyphis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cataglyphis viaticoides" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viaticoides">
<emphasis id="16EED2AE61F486C5C541A4F737FE7765" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Cataglyphis viaticoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a senior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="3985B64C6B6A0FF885955F359B70BEE3" authorityName="Atanassov" authorityYear="1982" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Cataglyphis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cataglyphis livida subsp. bulgarica" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="livida" subSpecies="bulgarica">
<emphasis id="68C324023FB3658A32E4A610CF9A8B9E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Cataglyphis livida bulgarica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Atanassov, 1982. It is known from few sites in East Rhodopes in Bulgaria (
<bibRefCitation id="3C7A22D4D5EF19EB41721A2456BA64F1" author="Atanassov, N." journalOrPublisher="Bulgarian Academy of Sciences, Sofia" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" refId="B7725616" refString="Atanassov, N., Dlussky, G. M., 1992. Fauna Bulgarica. 22. Hymenoptera, Formicidae. Bulgarian Academy of Sciences, Sofia" title="Fauna Bulgarica. 22. Hymenoptera, Formicidae" year="1992">Atanassov and Dlussky 1992</bibRefCitation>
) and its general distribution covers the south-eastern Balkans and Asia Minor (
<bibRefCitation id="76ED51CCE7F609A65BE48261CDE63EA0" author="Salata, S." journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" pagination="117 - 131" refId="B7725961" refString="Salata, S., Kiyani, H., Minaei, K., Borowiec, L., 2021. Taxonomic review of the Cataglyphis livida complex (Hymenoptera, Formicidae), with a description of a new species from Iran. ZooKeys 1010: 117 - 131" title="Taxonomic review of the Cataglyphis livida complex (Hymenoptera, Formicidae), with a description of a new species from Iran" volume="1010" year="2021">Salata et al. 2021</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
